    <h2 id="why-iron-anemia">Iron Deficiency Anemia: The Most Common Nutritional Deficiency in the World</h2>

    <p>Iron deficiency anemia affects approximately 1.2 billion people worldwide, making it the single most common nutritional deficiency on the planet. In the United States alone, an estimated 10 million people are iron-deficient, with 5 million meeting the clinical threshold for anemia. The condition disproportionately affects women of reproductive age, pregnant women, vegetarians, and endurance athletes — populations whose iron demands exceed what diet alone can typically provide.</p>

